  "title": "Senior Contracts Administrator/Specialist (Base Metals/Concentrates/Coal/Iron Ore/Oil)",
  "description": "<p><em><strong>*Seeking for a Senior Contracts Administrator/Specialist who has minimum 4 years of drafting or reviewing Contracts experience in Base Metals/Concentrates/Coal/Iron Ore/Oil*</strong></em></p><p><strong>THE COMPANY</strong></p><p>They are one of the esteemed names in the Commodities industry. Currently, they are looking for an experienced Senior Contracts Administrator/Specialist seeking for aspiring career in this industry!</p><p><strong>JOB RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></p><ul><li>Draft physical contracts based on deals</li><li>Review contracts from counterparties</li><li>Advice any necessary amendments and ensure corrections are indicated in the contracts</li><li>Work closely with Traders, Operators, Finance and other relevant departments</li><li>Any other ad-hoc or involvement in Projects</li></ul><p><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Business Studies/Finance/Banking/Economics/Commerce or any other relevant education</li><li>Minimum of 4 years of drafting or reviewing Contracts experience in Base Metals/Concentrates/Coal/Iron Ore/Oil</li><li>Excellent writing skills, attentive to details, proactive and organized</li></ul><p>If you will like to explore this opportunity, please email your resume in Microsoft Word format to <a href=\"mailto:marie@resolutehunter.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">marie@resolutehunter.com</a></p><p>We thank you for your interest and will contact shortlisted candidates for more detailed discussion.</p><p>For more job openings, please visit our website at https://resolutehunter.com/opportunities/</p><p>EA Licence 18C9105</p><p>EA Reg R1105305</p>",
